HEADWORD: Carpathian
<hw>Car*pa"thi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to a range of mountains in Austro-Hungary, called the Carpathians, which
partially inclose Hungary on the north, east, and south.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

